Full-Stack E-Commerce Architecture
1. Frontend

Browser / Mobile App

React.js / Next.js 

Pages:

Home / Product Listing

Product Detail

Cart / Checkout

User Authentication

Order History

Admin Panel (optional)

Communicates with Backend API via HTTP (REST or GraphQL)

Handles state (cart, user session, filters)

Shows notifications & validation (like “added to cart”)

2. Backend 

Node.js + Express (or any backend framework)

Responsibilities:

Authentication

Login, Signup

JWT token validation

Product Management

CRUD operations for products

Manage stock and images

Cart & Orders

Add/remove items

Checkout

Track order status

Payment

Integrate Stripe/PayPal

Confirm payment success/failure

Admin Dashboard

Manage products, users, orders

Security

Input validation

Authorization checks

Routes Example

/api/products        GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
/api/users           GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
/api/cart            GET, POST, DELETE
/api/orders          GET, POST
/api/auth/login      POST
/api/auth/register   POST

3. Database Layer

Stores all data

Users: name, email, password, role

Products: title, description, price, stock, images

Orders: userId, productId, quantity, status, payment info

Cart: userId, productId, quantity

Categories: product categories

Reviews: userId, productId, rating, comment

Database Choices

SQL: MySQL, PostgreSQL

NoSQL: MongoDB (often used with Node.js)

Optional caching: Redis

4. Deployment Layer

Frontend: Vercel / Netlify

Backend: Heroku / Render / AWS EC2

Database: MongoDB Atlas / AWS RDS

Storage: S3 / Cloudinary for product images

5. Flow Diagram (Text Version)
[User Browser / Mobile App]
           |
           v
    [Frontend (React/Next.js)]
           |
   HTTP Requests / REST API
           |
           v
      [Backend (Node.js/Express)]
           |
   -----------------------------
   |           |               |
   v           v               v
[Auth]     [Products]      [Orders/Cart]
           |
           v
      [Database (MongoDB/MySQL)]


Optional Admin Panel Flow

[Admin Browser]
       |
       v
  [Frontend Admin Dashboard]
       |
       v
   [Backend APIs]
       |
       v
    [Database]



